=What does "[[:Category:Open | Open]]" Mean and How Does it Apply to [[Cooperatives]]?=

All manner of cooperatives exist in the world today, from two people sharing a donkey all the way up to powerful institutions where the members are gigantic multinational corporations.

When it comes to legal definitions in most jurisdictions  a cooperative is organized in order to benefit the members.  When that ceases to happen, either the member leaves or the cooperative itself ceases to function or even exist.  

Peer-to-peer theory starts with the individual, and at the root of an Open Cooperative, then, we must ask ourselves: 

To what end does it serve the individual members of a cooperative to maintain principles of Openness in their business interactions?

Here are some of the subjects to which the concept of Openness has been applied:

*Accounting
*Membership
*Standards

